---
description: Observability, monitoring, logging, and analytics rules for SalesIQ
globs: backend/app/core/**, backend/app/services/**, backend/app/ai/**
---

Observability scope:
- Structured logs with correlation IDs for all API requests and background tasks.
- AI response monitoring: latency, token usage, model ID, error rates per OpenAI call.
- Call pipeline monitoring: transcription latency, analysis latency, prediction latency.
- Real-time system: WebSocket connection count, Socket.IO room membership, pub/sub event rates.
- Business analytics: calls per tenant, conversion rates, agent scores, prediction accuracy.

Logging rules:
- Use `structlog` for all backend logging — JSON-formatted, machine-parseable.
- Every log entry on a request path must include: `request_id`, `tenant_id`, `user_id` (if available), `level`, `message`, `duration_ms`.
- Every AI call log must include: `model`, `prompt_tokens`, `completion_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `latency_ms`, `call_id` (if applicable).
- Every Celery task log must include: `task_id`, `task_name`, `call_id`, `tenant_id`, `status`.
- Log at `INFO` for successful flows, `WARNING` for recoverable issues, `ERROR` for failures with full context.
- Do not log PII: transcript text, customer names, phone numbers, email addresses — mask or redact in log pipelines.

Key metrics to instrument (SalesIQ-specific):
- `call.initiated` — counter per tenant
- `call.completed` — counter per tenant
- `transcription.latency_ms` — histogram
- `analysis.latency_ms` — histogram (GPT-4o call analysis)
- `prediction.latency_ms` — histogram (GPT-4o deal prediction)
- `guidance.latency_ms` — histogram (real-time guidance generation < 2s target)
- `websocket.active_connections` — gauge
- `celery.task.failed` — counter per task type
- `openai.tokens_used` — counter per model per tenant

Alerting priorities:
- CRITICAL: Twilio webhook handler down, OpenAI API errors above 5% threshold, Celery worker queue depth > 100.
- WARNING: Real-time guidance latency > 3s, transcription failure rate > 2%, Redis pub/sub lag.
- INFO: Daily call volume summaries, prediction accuracy drift.

Analytics endpoints (already in `app/api/v1/analytics.py`):
- Dashboard KPIs: total calls, conversion rate, active agents, pipeline value, AI score trends.
- Conversion funnel: leads by status stage.
- Agent leaderboard: ranked by calls, conversion rate, average score.
- Call trends: volume and duration over time.
- Prediction accuracy: predicted vs actual win rate over time.

Do not:
- Use `print()` statements for production diagnostics — always use `structlog`.
- Expose internal error details or stack traces to API clients — log them, return sanitized messages.
- Add observability as an afterthought — include logging and task instrumentation in new features by default.
- Alert on every warning — design alerts to be actionable and avoid alert fatigue.
